    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieves level 2 against a required level 4; however, the team judged that the ASTM F1717 standardized protocol provides sufficient reproducibility and that the single-condition limitation is mitigated by the multi-laboratory design (N=11 across two labs). Overall assurance level declared High based on strong quantitative validation outcomes (all QoIs within acceptance bounds) and robust software and model verification evidence. The single factor shortfall is considered acceptable given the conservative acceptance criteria applied to output comparison.",
